Updates via SVN

= General information =

SVN is a Control version program, sucessor to the CVS.

SVN is supported by php5 as EXPERIMENTAL. In future versions of PHP,
methods of SVN class may change.

This program use SVN functions to update the most important scripts
and themplates, that are changed frecuently, adn this is the most
easy way to update the program and fix bugs.

= How to operate =

The Working directory (/updates) handles a updated copies of the
scripts that are updated frecuently. These files are updated via SVN
to the repository using svn_update()

Once installed, the Installer performs first an svn_checkout() in
order to download the files at first time. Once updated, the
Administrator have the option to see the version, the diff between
version installer and other options, before installing on Application dir.